+#### D.4.0 Authority matrix — the `/admin/*` route surface is NOT one permission domain
+
+The current web-ui `/admin/*` surface is not a single permission class. Each handler is one of three distinct authority requirements; the plan's route-level changes are per-class, not per-handler-uniform.
+
+| Authority class | Means | Routes (current code paths) | Wire bearer used | Required session predicate |
+|---|---|---|---|---|
+| **experiment-admin** | session worker is in this experiment's `admins` group | `/admin/` (index), `/admin/tasks/`, `/admin/tasks/<T>/reassign`, `/admin/dispatch_mode/`, `/admin/events/`, `/admin/ideas/*`, `/admin/variants/*`, `/admin/work-refs/`, `/admin/terminate`, `/admin/workers/` (list/detail/reissue — see footnote), `/admin/groups/` (list/detail/add-member/remove-member), `/admin/artifacts/` ([`routes/admin/observability.py`](../../reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/admin/observability.py), [`routes/admin/actions.py`](../../reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/admin/actions.py), [`routes/admin/work_refs.py`](../../reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/admin/work_refs.py), [`routes/admin_artifacts.py`](../../reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/admin_artifacts.py), [`routes/admin_groups.py`](../../reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/admin_groups.py), most of [`routes/admin_workers.py`](../../reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/admin_workers.py)) | Session bearer (read + group-gated worker ops); `app.state.admin_store` for the subset of mutations still admin-principal-gated at the wire (`register_worker`, `reissue_credential`, `register_group`, `delete_group`) | session.worker_id ∈ `admins` (transitive) |
+| **deployment-admin** | session worker is in `admins` AND the web-ui is configured with `app.state.admin_store` (the deployment admin bearer plumbing) | (no UI-only routes today; every deployment-admin operation is exposed through experiment-admin pages and proxies via `app.state.admin_store` — e.g. `register_worker` on `/admin/workers/register`, `reissue_credential` on `/admin/workers/<id>/reissue`, `register_group` on `/admin/groups/register`, `delete_group` on `/admin/groups/<g>/delete`) | `app.state.admin_store` (deployment admin bearer) | session.worker_id ∈ `admins` AND `app.state.admin_store is not None` |
+| **control-plane-admin** | deployment-wide cross-experiment surface — only available when web-ui is configured with `--control-plane-url` | `/admin/experiments/` (cross-experiment dashboard), per-experiment lifecycle ops ([`routes/admin_experiments.py`](../../reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/admin_experiments.py)) | `app.state.control_plane` client (separate deployment-wide credential) | session.worker_id ∈ `admins` AND `app.state.control_plane is not None` |
+
+Two consequences this matrix forces the plan to acknowledge:
+
+1. **The single `require_admin` route guard is necessary but NOT sufficient.** It correctly blocks non-admin sessions from every `/admin/*` surface, but it does NOT distinguish experiment-admin from deployment-admin from control-plane-admin authority. Mutations that proxy through `app.state.admin_store` or `app.state.control_plane` inherit those clients' deployment-wide authority on any successful POST. An experiment admin who can access `/admin/workers/register` becomes a deployment-admin proxy: they can call `register_worker` against the deployment via the web-ui's bearer. This is the trust-delegation footgun §10.3 acknowledges; this plan does NOT eliminate it. The mitigations in scope are:
